Java implementation of the CoAP protocol (draft 08)
===================================================
see: http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-core-coap-08

usable for both clients and servers including extensions:

* CoAP observe (draft 06)
-----------------------
see: http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-core-observe-06

* CoAP block-transfer (draft 04, partially)
-----------------------------------------
see: http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-core-block-04

For now, the blockwise transfer only works for clients receiving blockwise responses


Maven
=====

To use the latest released nCoAP Maven artifact add the following to your pom.xml

<repositories>
...
    <repository>
        <id>itm-maven-repository-releases-site</id>
        <url>https://maven.itm.uni-luebeck.de/content/repositories/releases/</url>
    </repository>
...
</repositories>

....

<dependencies>
...
    <dependency>
        <groupId>de.uniluebeck.itm</groupId>
        <artifactId>ncoap</artifactId>
        <version>1.0.2</version>
    </dependency>
...
</dependencies>


Documentation
=============

The documentation is available at http://media.itm.uni-luebeck.de/people/kleine/maven/ncoap/

To get started with using the nCoAP framework I refer to https://github.com/okleine/SimpleCoapApplications.
